04242nam a22007095i 9780813564753DE-B159720191221113333.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||191221s2014    nju    fo  d z      eng d  a97808135647537 a10.36019/97808135647532doi  a(DE-B1597)526241  a(OCoLC)884016242  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  anjucUS-NJ 7aEDU0000002bisacsh1 aMcCormick, Richard L., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut.10aRaised at Rutgers :bA President's Story /cRichard L. McCormick. 1aNew Brunswick, NJ : bRutgers University Press, c[2014] 4cÂ©2014  a1 online resource (304 p.) :b22 photographs  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda0 aRivergate Regionals Collection00tFrontmatter -- tCONTENTS -- tPreface and Acknowledgments -- t1. Six Scenes from a University Presidency -- t2. Coming of Age at Rutgers -- t3. A Difficult First Year as Rutgers President -- t4. The Academic Heart of the Matter -- t5. Intercollegiate Athletics -- t6. Rutgers and New Jersey -- t7. Getting a Medical School, Concluding a Presidency -- t8. Reflections on Leading Rutgers -- tSources -- tIndex0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aIn Raised at Rutgers, Richard L. McCormick tells what it is like to run a major state university and vividly portrays the often contentious environment in which a university president operates today. He unsparingly recounts his decade of leadership, including his own missteps-those we know about and those we didn't-as he strove to obtain adequate resources for the university, to overhaul the often confusing organization of the New Brunswick campus, to manage the growth and success of intercollegiate athletics, and to deepen Rutgers's acceptance of its obligations as the state university of New Jersey. With understandable pride, McCormick recalls and relates Rutgers's academic achievements during his presidency, including a renewed focus on undergraduate education and a significant increase in funding for research. Most dramatically, he chronicles the University's protracted efforts to reclaim Robert Wood Johnson Medical School (and ultimately to acquire most of UMDNJ), a goal that was finally realized with crucial help from Governor Chris Christie and former governor Tom Kean. Among the most honest accounts ever written of a college presidency, Raised at Rutgers takes the reader inside one of the best, and liveliest, public universities in America and highlights many of the most critical issues facing higher education today.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Dez 2019) 7aEDUCATION / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertRUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2015z978311066331008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertRUP eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311066615140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780813564753423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780813564753.jpg  a978-3-11-066331-0  RUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  a978-3-11-066615-1  RUP eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA14ALL  aPDA16SSH  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA1ALL  aPDA2  aPDA2HUM  aPDA5EBK  aPDA7ENG